  2. ‌Preface‌

    1. ‌References‌

      This document refers to the Unified POS Version 1.13. This specification can be downloaded here http://www.nrf-arts.org/content/unified-pos.


    2. ‌Tags and abbreviations‌

      Type identifiers given for parameters and attributes refer to Javascript types.


      1. ‌Display‌

        The tag (display) marks data designed for displaying to the user. These are values like translated texts or preformatted amounts. The mobile attendant software should not interpret these values.


  3. ‌Introduction‌

    1. ‌Scope‌

      Mobile attendant devices like tablets or phones need to communicate with the Vynamic™ Self-Service (formerly known as TPiSCAN) server and VynamicTM Self- Service terminals. Vynamic™ Self-Service terminals will be called „lanes“ in this document, regardless of their physical setup as scan&bag stations, pay stations, scan stations or other.

      This document describes the interface for connecting mobile attendant devices to lanes as well as to the server. In a productive environment, lanes may communicate with multiple mobile and stationary attendant terminals. Equally, an attendant terminal, mobile or stationary, communicates simultaneously with multiple lanes. In the remainder of this document, communication is without restriction described between one mobile attendant terminal with one lane.

      The interfaces are described in their logical structure (semantics). Technical realization, of which there may be several, will not be considered here.

      Mobile attendant devices are being developed and extended in several stages. The interface in this document shows the full scope, while the actual implementation in any product may have restrictions.


    2. ‌Requirements‌

      On the mobile attendant station (mobile AS), the following functions shall be offered:

      • login of an attendant

      • display the general status of a lane

      • display and respond to atomic attendant requests, including confirmation and input via calculator

      • display and reset peripheral status

      • execute attendant functions, such as coupon entry, price override and other

      • display the virtual receipt of a lane.

      Due to expected technical restrictions, the interface cannot use polymorphic type structures.


    3. ‌General Design Ideas‌

      1. ‌Client-Server and Status-Changed-Event‌

        Communication between lane and mobile AS works according to a client-server concept. The lane represents the server, and mobile AS the client. Communication is via http(s) protocol with JSON objects. The mobile AS has to poll all lanes to check if a lane status has changed. The lanes would be able to communicate a status-change-event via UDP,

        webserver part of the REST interface



        but browser based webapps are unable to catch such events. Further details are given in the appendix.


      2. ‌User Rights‌

        User rights are evaluated on the lane. When the mobile AS is requesting “GET status”, the call contains the user ID of the current attendant. The response from the lane will indicate, which actions shall be available to the user.


      3. ‌Multi Language Support‌

        Translation is processed on the lane. The mobile AS transmits the user’s language with the get status call. Texts received from the lane shall be translated as far as available.


    4. ‌Prerequisites in configuration to enable the webserver part of the REST interface‌

      1. The REST interface must be enabled in the workflow.

      2. In the Customization Center, the following webapps need to be enabled: Vynamic Self-Service Server REST

      Vynamic Self-Service Lane REST


      Furthermore, to enable the REST webapps, the RemoteControlConfig_default.xml is required. In this config,

      <remotecontrol enabled=”true”/>

      must be set for all run_composites where it should be used. If you want to use it on any lane, you have to use it on the server as well. It makes no sense to have it only on server or only on lanes.


      In addition on store server it is required to load the ServerRemoteControl in ServerConfig_default.xml:

      <module load="true" name="ServerRemoteControl"/>


      In case the remote control devices are able to receive and process UDP network packets, the following can be added to RemoteControlConfig_default.xml:

      <statuschangedevents ipaddress="230.0.0.42" port="4447"/> Then the devices have to register for that broadcast address to receive the packets. The payload of the packet is the hostname of the lane whose lane status has changed.

      This has the advantage that such devices get informed about lane status changes immediately. Otherwise the devices have to poll the lane status permanently.


  4. ‌Specification of the Vynamic™ Self-Service Server REST Interface‌

    1. ‌Server Service‌

      Server Base URL

      https://{server host}:{port}/iSCAN-Server-REST with BASIC Http Authentication


      This service provides data about the Vynamic™ Self-Service server.

      1. ‌GET /lanes‌

        Use to retrieve a list of lanes which the mobile AS shall interact with. Response status code: 200

        Response body: An array of type LaneContact


        Parameter

        Name

        Comment

        attendantId

        Unique name of the mobile AS.

        e.g. „MobileAttendant01“


        Example:

        https://127.0.0.1:13201/iSCAN-Server-REST/lanes?attendantId=MobileAttendant01


    2. ‌JSON object LaneContact‌

      This object keeps address information of a lane.

      Attribute

      Name

      Type

      Comment

      laneName(display)

      String

      Name of the lane as it shall be displayed on the AS.


      hostName

      String

      IP address or lane’s host name (as configured in AttendantEnvironmentConfig), e.g. „172.18.103.15“,

      „debln253“, „debln253.wincor-nixdorf.com“

      port

      int

      Port to contact the lane via http, e.g „13102“ (since 13.0 only https available)

      httpsPort

      int

      Port to contact the lane via https, e.g „13202“


  5. ‌Specification of the Vynamic™ Self-Service Lane REST Interface‌

    1. ‌Lane Service‌

      Lane Base URL

      https://{lane host}:{port}/iSCAN-Lane-REST with BASIC Http Authentication


      This service provides data about the Vynamic™ Self-Service lane device.

      1. ‌GET /lane‌

        This operation returns general information of the lane, independent of its status.


        Response status code: 200 Response body: LaneInformation


        Parameter

        None


        Example:

        https://127.0.0.1:13202/iSCAN-Lane-REST/lane


      2. ‌GET /lane/status‌

        This operation returns the status of the lane.


        Response status code: 200 Response body: LaneStatus


        Parameter

        Name

        Comment

        language

        ISO code of the user’s language, e.g. „de“. This is used to translate device names.

        withTransaction

        True, if the returned lane status has to contain the complete virtual receipt relevant information.


        ‌Example:

        https://127.0.0.1:13202/iSCAN-Lane-REST/lane/status?withTransaction=true&language=de


      3. ‌POST /lane/request/{requestId}/confirm?value={value}‌

        This operation confirms a request which is pending on the lane.


        Response status code: 204 or 404 (when value is empty or contains special character like ? or .)

        Response body: empty


        Parameter

        Name

        Comment

        requestId

        Unique ID of the request. It corresponds to the attribute id of Request object.


        value

        The meaning of this value depends on the inquiry type of the request.

        For SelectOptionInquiry it contains the ID of the chosen option.

        For InputValueInquiry it contains the entered String representation.

        For ScanningProblemInquiry it contains the ID values of the chosen item details.

        Multiple occurrences of this parameter are possible. Without this parameter (except for scanning problem) the default input/option are assumed.


        Example:

        https://127.0.0.1:13202/iSCAN-Lane-REST/lane/request/26c6e273-ef1d-4c59-b765- db086d0a64c5/confirm


      4. ‌POST /lane/device/{deviceId}/reset‌

        Use this operation to reset the status of a peripheral.


        Response status code: 204 or 404 (when value is empty or contains special character like ? or .)

        Response body: empty


        Parameter

        Name

        Comment

        deviceId

        Unique ID of the peripheral. It corresponds to the attribute deviceId of DeviceStatus object.


        Example:

        https://127.0.0.1:13202/iSCAN-Lane-REST/lane/device/printer/reset


      5. ‌POST /lane/open‌

        Use this operation to open the lane.


        Response status code: 204 or 405 (when user does not have openLane permission) Response body: empty


        Parameter

        None


        ‌Example:

        https://127.0.0.1:13202/iSCAN-Lane-REST/lane/open


      6. ‌POST /lane/close‌

        Use this operation to close the lane.


        Response status code: 204 or 405 (when user does not have closeLane permission) Response body: empty

        Parameter

        None


        Example:

        https://127.0.0.1:13202/iSCAN-Lane-REST/lane/close


      7. ‌DELETE /lane/vr-entry/{entryId}‌

        Use this operation to remove an entry from the virtual receipt.


        Response status code: 204 or 403 (when entryId is empty or contains special character like ? or .) or 405 (when user does not have voidSelectedEntry permission)

        Response body: empty


        Parameter

        Name

        Comment

        entryId

        The entry-id to delete. Can be obtained from the lane status.


        Example:

        https://127.0.0.1:13202/iSCAN-Lane-REST/lane/vr-entry/item_000001


      8. ‌POST /lane/bay/{bayNumber}/change-to‌

        Use this operation to switch to a different bay for a tunnel lane with multiple bays.


        Response status code: 204 or 404 (when bayNumber is non numeric or empty) or 405 (when user does not have one of startChangeBaggingArea, startWithNextBaggingAreaBay or switchToNextBaggingAreaBay permission) Response body: empty


        ‌Parameter

        Name

        Comment

        bayNumber

        A value of 0 computes the next bagging area. The active bagging area can be found in the result of /lane/status


        Example:

        https://127.0.0.1:13202/iSCAN-Lane-REST/lane/bay/2/change-to


      9. ‌POST /lane/scan‌

        Sends a scanner event to the lane.


        Response status code: 200 or 417 (when scanData is missing) Response body: ScannedResult


        Parameter

        Name

        Comment

        language

        ISO code of the user’s language, e.g. „de“

        It is used only to present a possible error message.


        scanDataType

        The type of the scanned code, as described in document “UnifiedPOS Specification v1.13.pdf” (page 1200)

        It can be a numeric value which tells Vynamic™ Self- Service the barcode type.


        scanData

        The data read from the scanner as described in document “UnifiedPOS Specification v1.13.pdf” (page 1198)

        It consists of a 1 character prefix (which is internally not used except for logging) and the barcode.

        remoteId

        An optional identifier of the initiating device.


        Example:

        https://127.0.0.1:13202/iSCAN-Lane-REST/lane/scan?scanData=04000539322402


      10. ‌GET /lane/request/{requestId}/big-picture‌

        Returns a picture for a request in case of scanning problem.


        Response status code: 200 or 404 (if requestId is empty or contains special character like ? or .)

        Response body: Picture


        Parameter

        Name

        Comment

        requestId

        Unique ID of the request. It corresponds to the attribute id of Request object.


        Example:

        https://127.0.0.1:13202/iSCAN-Lane-REST/lane/request/68b6a1e3-1f28-4ba0-b2fc- 66e73fedd6eb/big-picture

    3. ‌JSON object LaneStatus‌


      Attribute

      Name

      Type

      Comment


      exclusiveControlledBy


      String

      Contains the ID of the lane’s exclusive controller. This may be an attendant station or the lane itself.

      Null means the lane is not being exclusively controlled.


      posIsOffline


      boolean

      True, if the POS on the lane is offline. That may have to be displayed on the mobile AS.


      stateHint (display)


      String

      Contains translated text for the phase of the lane or current sale transaction, e.g. “Paying”, “Scanning”, “Waiting”, “Closed” to be displayed by MA


      Attribute

      Name

      Type

      Comment


      state


      String

      Contains the phase of the lane or current sale transaction as String Representation. Possible values are:

      selectedBay

      int

      Currently selected packing bay

      readyForScanning

      boolean

      True if ISCAN is ready to accept barcodes


      requestCount


      int

      Number of requests pending on the lane including (if any) the one transmitted as open.

      • CLOSED

      • OPENING

      • NO_TRANSACTION

      • SCANNING

      • PAYING

      • TRANSACTION_FINISHING

      • CLOSING


      References

      Name

      Type

      Comment


      openRequest


      Request

      If a request is pending on the lane, this contains the next request to be processed.

      deviceStates

      Array of DeviceStatus

      A list of the peripherals’ statuses.


      currentTransaction


      Transaction

      If a transaction is open or finishing on the lane and if withTransaction parameter true in get status, this contains the transaction.

    5. ‌JSON object ScannedResult‌


      Attribute

      Name

      Type

      Comment

      rejected

      boolean

      False, if the scancode was processed. True otherwise.


      text(display)


      String

      A textual representation of the reason for the rejection, null if the scancode was not rejected

    6. ‌JSON object TransactionEntry‌


      Attribute

      Name

      Type

      Comment


      id


      String

      Identifier of the entry. Corresponds to the attribute entryId in the Vynamic™ Self- Service -POS interface.


      Attribute

      Name

      Type

      Comment


      entryType


      String

      The type of the entry.


      Possible values are:

      More values will follow in later Vynamic™ Self-Service versions. The mobile software should implement a default behavior for unknown values.


      lines(display)

      Array of String

      The texts which are displayed on the virtual receipt.

      amount(display)

      String

      The amount related to this entry.


      voidState


      String

      Unique ID of the “void status” of the entry. Can be used to distinguish rendering.

      “to-be-voided” – the entry is marked for later cancellation

      “voided” – the entry has been voided from the totals and remains as a reminder “voiding” – the entry is nullifying another

      skipped

      boolean

      Information for rendering. True if item was skipped from bagging on the lane.

      • item

      • expectedItem

      • priceReduction

      • customer

      • customerInfo

      • scanningProblems

      • separator

      • subTotal

      • tender

      • text

      • tax

    7. ‌JSON object DeviceStatus‌


      Attribute

      Name

      Type

      Comment


      deviceId


      String

      Unique ID of the peripheral, to which this device refers to, e.g. “printer”, “coin dispenser”, “note acceptor”


      Attribute

      Name

      Type

      Comment


      name (display)

      String

      Name of the peripheral, e.g. “Printer”, “CoinDispenser”, „NoteAcceptor“


      status


      String

      Unique ID of the status of the peripheral:

      „g“ is green – ready for operation

      „y“ is yellow – operational, but a problem was detected.

      „r“ is red – out of operation


      text (display)


      String

      A textual representation of the status, e.g.

      „Printer near end of paper“, „Coin dispenser empty“ or null

    8. ‌JSON object Request‌

      An attendant request represents an inquiry to the supervisor (for further reference consult the Vynamic™ Self-Service manual). It may be blocking the user’s interaction with the lane, or non-blocking. While a blocking request is pending, the user cannot continue in the current sale process and waits for a reaction of the attendant. Both request types are responded to in the same manner. Blocking requests may be rendered differently on the mobile AS to attract the immediate attention of the supervisor.


      Attribute

      Name

      Type

      Comment

      id

      String

      Unique ID for this request.


      requestId


      String

      Human readable but technical (non translated) description of the reason, e.g. “customerIsInactive”

      liveStart

      long

      Milliseconds since 01.01.1970 when the request was created

      blocking

      boolean

      True, if the requst is blocking.


      Referenzen

      Name

      Type

      Comment

      inquiry

      Inquiry

      The inquiry to be answered to by the attendant.


    9. ‌JSON object Inquiry‌

      Referenzen

    12. ‌JSON object InputValueInquiry‌

      Represents user data input, which is usually done via a keyboard (physical or projected to the touch screen).


      References

      Name

      Type

      Comment

      inputMethod

      InputMethod

      Contains the InputMethod, which describes the user input.


      Attribute

      Name

      Type

      Comment


      enabled


      boolean

      True, if the client shall allow input for this inquiry. If false, the inquiry shall only be displayed.


      defaultText(display)


      String

      A description of the default answer, e.g. ”Ok”, “Yes”, “No”, “Confirm”


      defaultValue


      String

      The default value for the inquiry. If the default answer is selected, this value shall be put to the attribute value of operation confirmRequest.

      defaultEnabled

      boolean

      True, if a default answer is allowed and available.


    13. ‌JSON object ScanningProblemInquiry‌

      This object represents the item details which the lane was able to establish related to a scanning problem. Several details may exist per problem and the user may choose none, one, or more of them to confirm and void the request.


      References

      Name

      Type

      Comment

      preview

      Picture

      The smaller previous image of the object, which causes the problem.


      scanCodeDetails

      Array of ScanCodeDetails

      Optionally contains details for the scanning problem, of which the user may choose.

      defaultOption

      Option

      Optional. Refers to the default answer.


      References

      Name

      Type

      Comment


      Options


      Array of Options

      Optional. A list of options (e. g. to respond to a volume error) of which one needs to be chosen as answer to the request.

    15. ‌JSON object ScanCodeDetails‌

      This object represents the item details which the lane was able to establish related to a scanning problem. Several details may exist per problem and the user may choose none, one, or more of them to confirm and void the request.

      Consecutive calls to get status may show other data in the ScanCodeDetails structure.


      Attribute

      Name

      Type

      Comment

      id

      String

      Unique ID of the detail

      description(display)

      String

      Descriptive text, translated where possible.

    17. ‌JSON object InputMethod‌

      This object describes, how the user shall input her answer.


      Attribute

      Name

      Type

      Comment

      cancelAllowed

      boolean

      Whether the opportunity shall be given to cancel the input.

      defaultResponse

      String

      Contains the predefined value. May be null.


      maxInputLength


      long

      Maximum number of characters allowed for the answer. For numeric inputs (currency value), the decimal delimiter does not count. Use zero for unlimited entry.


      minInputLength


      long

      Minimum number of characters allowed for the answer. For numeric inputs (currency value), the decimal delimiter does not count. Use zero for unlimited entry.

      emptyValueAllowed

      boolean

      True, if empty response is allowed. Price input requests must never be empty.

      keyedInInput

      boolean

      True, if input shall be keyed in.

      msrInput

      boolean

      True, if the magnetic swipe reader shall be usable for providing the input.


      scannerInput


      boolean

      True, if the scanner shall be usable for providing the input.

      At least one of scannerInput, msrInput, keyedInInput must be set to true.

      Validator

      String

      A regular expression to validate input. May be null.


      Attribute

      Name

      Type

      Comment

      enterByMaxlengthAu tomatically


      boolean

      If true, the response shall be sent when the maximum number of characters is reached.

    23. ‌JSON object DateInputMethod‌

      This object represents the request for a date to be input by the user.


      Attribute

      Name

      Type

      Comment


      dateMask


      String

      Contains a string to display while not all digits have been input. Input is done in language specific orientation. The string consist at least of an arbitrary concatenation of dayMask, monthMask, and yearMask and an arbitrary set of further characters in between these well- known parts.


      Attribute

      Name

      Type

      Comment


      dayMask


      String

      Identifies the number of characters for day input as well as the characters to show while not all digits have been input.


      monthMask


      String

      Identifies the number of characters for month input as well as the characters to show while not all digits have been input.


      yearMask


      String

      Identifies the number of characters for year input as well as the characters to show while not all digits have been input.


      formatPattern


      String

      Contains the date format pattern to display (to allow the user to verify) the fully entered date. May be null.


    24. ‌Example lane status‌


      {

      "deviceStates": [

      {

      "deviceId": "printer", "name": "Printer",

      "status": "g", "text": null

      },

      {

      "deviceId": "remote server", "name": "Remote server", "status": "g",

      "text": "Remote server reachable"

    25. ‌The Meaning of Strings in Value Inputs‌

      The input methods confirmRequest and confirmInquiry expect a String type response. The String represents a value depending on the InputMethod following this table:


      Parameter

      InputMethod

      Type

      String Representation


      WholeNumberInputMethod


      long

      A Long type value without decimals nor leading zeros., e.g.

      „1“, „42“

      EANInputMethod

      String

      An EAN as String, e.g. „100“,

      „4001478015721“

      TextInputMethod

      String

      A simple text.

      PinInputMethod

      String

      A simple text.


      PriceInputMethod


      long

      A price as whole number, resulting from multiplying the actual value by ten to the power of x, where x equals fractionDigits.


      DateInputMethod


      Date

      A date as formatted String, using the Java SimpleDateFormat("dd/MM/yyyy")
